You sure?

00:13:33.104 --> 00:13:35.315 position:50% align:center
'Cause it's about to
start, so if you need--

00:13:35.398 --> 00:13:36.566 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:39.027 --> 00:13:41.237 position:50% align:center
[AOI chuckles]

00:13:41.321 --> 00:13:44.574 position:50% align:center
Look at that! Blue lights.

00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:47.410 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA]
Those shoes.

00:13:47.494 --> 00:13:50.372 position:50% align:center
You only wear them for special
occasions, isn't that right?

00:13:50.455 --> 00:13:52.499 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:13:52.582 --> 00:13:54.000 position:50% align:center
Yeah...

00:13:56.044 --> 00:13:57.128 position:50% align:center
I made these for you!

00:13:57.212 --> 00:14:00.131 position:50% align:center
I know how much
you like blue, Aoi.

00:14:00.215 --> 00:14:02.509 position:50% align:center
Wow!

00:14:02.592 --> 00:14:04.928 position:50% align:center
[BULLY A] No way,
your brother made those?

00:14:05.011 --> 00:14:07.806 position:50% align:center
[BULLY B]
Is he a girl or somethin'?

00:14:10.308 --> 00:14:12.519 position:50% align:center
I hate these dumb gloves!

00:14:16.815 --> 00:14:19.776 position:50% align:center
[music plays]

00:14:19.859 --> 00:14:21.569 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA gasps]

00:14:21.653 --> 00:14:25.365 position:50% align:center
Listen! They're playing
Noka's favorite song, Mommy!

00:14:25.448 --> 00:14:27.158 position:50% align:center
That takes me back.

00:14:38.962 --> 00:14:41.172 position:50% align:center
It's a ribbon!

00:14:41.256 --> 00:14:45.468 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO] Yep, this is
undoubtedly Ikuto's show!

00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:47.303 position:50% align:center
Isn't it great?

00:14:49.931 --> 00:14:52.142 position:50% align:center
[AOI crying]

00:14:52.225 --> 00:14:55.270 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA]
Aoi, are those tears I see?

00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:59.190 position:50% align:center
Pretty sure you teased me
for that three minutes ago.

00:14:59.274 --> 00:15:01.151 position:50% align:center
[AOI]
I know, but I...

00:15:01.234 --> 00:15:04.112 position:50% align:center
I so want Ikuto to win.

00:15:04.195 --> 00:15:05.572 position:50% align:center
It's just...

00:15:05.655 --> 00:15:10.118 position:50% align:center
...I want him to see how
amazing he is and celebrate it!

00:15:10.201 --> 00:15:12.454 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow. So good.

00:15:12.537 --> 00:15:16.416 position:50% align:center
He gave it his all,
and he's here to win!

00:15:17.625 --> 00:15:21.588 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA] Crossing boundaries.
Harmony between genders.

00:15:21.671 --> 00:15:24.716 position:50% align:center
Pattern upon pattern
of tartan and pin checks.

00:15:24.799 --> 00:15:27.552 position:50% align:center
Reminiscent of Great Britain.

00:15:27.635 --> 00:15:29.679 position:50% align:center
An outfit which was
obviously designed

00:15:29.763 --> 00:15:33.266 position:50% align:center
so that only a tall model
could pull it off successfully.

00:15:33.350 --> 00:15:35.560 position:50% align:center
My guess is...

00:15:35.643 --> 00:15:38.688 position:50% align:center
...this collection is about
to take us around the world.

00:15:38.772 --> 00:15:40.065 position:50% align:center
[GIRL A]
That's so cute!

00:15:40.148 --> 00:15:42.942 position:50% align:center
[GIRL B] I agree.
I'd totally wear that!

00:15:43.026 --> 00:15:45.737 position:50% align:center
His concept was crystal
clear right off the bat.

00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:48.782 position:50% align:center
Ikuto, well done!

00:15:48.865 --> 00:15:50.533 position:50% align:center
[ICHIKA]
You're not gonna cry, Mommy?

00:15:50.617 --> 00:15:52.327 position:50% align:center
Oh, who, me?

00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:54.496 position:50% align:center
Mommy's not your sisters.

00:15:54.579 --> 00:15:57.374 position:50% align:center
What?! Mother!
I'm not crying, okay?

00:15:57.457 --> 00:15:59.793 position:50% align:center
You're thinking of Honoka,
that's her thing.

00:15:59.876 --> 00:16:01.294 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA grunts]

00:16:01.378 --> 00:16:04.589 position:50% align:center
[AOI groans]
Don't pinch me!

00:16:04.673 --> 00:16:06.508 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA]
Mom never cries.

00:16:06.591 --> 00:16:09.052 position:50% align:center
Even Ikuto said he's
never seen her cry.

00:16:09.135 --> 00:16:12.931 position:50% align:center
Sure I do. Believe me,
I'm sobbing in my heart.

00:16:13.014 --> 00:16:14.849 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA]
Yeah, okay.

00:16:14.933 --> 00:16:16.726 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Your walk was great!

00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:17.811 position:50% align:center
Just keep that up!

00:16:17.894 --> 00:16:19.688 position:50% align:center
It's perfect!

00:16:19.771 --> 00:16:21.564 position:50% align:center
[gasps] 'Kay.

00:16:22.524 --> 00:16:24.984 position:50% align:center
[CROWD gasps]

00:16:25.068 --> 00:16:28.196 position:50% align:center
[FUMIYO] So the second and
third outfits were Scandinavia.

00:16:28.279 --> 00:16:30.532 position:50% align:center
And the fourth outfit is Italy.

00:16:30.615 --> 00:16:32.117 position:50% align:center
Elegant palazzo pants

00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:35.995 position:50% align:center
featuring strips of
peek-a-boo Sicilian lace.

00:16:36.079 --> 00:16:39.332 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA]
Then the next up will be...

00:16:39.416 --> 00:16:40.959 position:50% align:center
I knew it!

00:16:41.042 --> 00:16:42.377 position:50% align:center
[FUMIYO]
Wow.

00:16:42.460 --> 00:16:45.880 position:50% align:center
He used a traditional Italian
embroidery method, too.

00:16:45.964 --> 00:16:48.466 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA] Society tends to
praise the unpredictable,

00:16:48.550 --> 00:16:51.302 position:50% align:center
which makes sense,
but I tend to think

00:16:51.386 --> 00:16:53.847 position:50% align:center
with a collection like this,
predictability is proof

00:16:53.930 --> 00:16:57.392 position:50% align:center
that the idea is grounded
in a clear intention.

00:16:57.475 --> 00:16:59.060 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU] Where do
you think will be next?

00:16:59.144 --> 00:17:01.354 position:50% align:center
Don't talk to me.

00:17:01.438 --> 00:17:03.106 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU]
Here it comes.

00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:04.941 position:50% align:center
Japan.

00:17:06.026 --> 00:17:07.318 position:50% align:center
[HARUKA]
The runway--

00:17:07.402 --> 00:17:09.195 position:50% align:center
it's a blinding white.

00:17:09.279 --> 00:17:13.533 position:50% align:center
But somehow my legs
are moving on their own.

00:17:13.616 --> 00:17:16.119 position:50% align:center
The top is made with
comfy thick fabric

00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:18.580 position:50% align:center
and the shorts are
a stretchy denim.

00:17:18.663 --> 00:17:22.250 position:50% align:center
The sleeves are lace,
so my arms feel light.

00:17:22.334 --> 00:17:25.795 position:50% align:center
That first outfit,
and now this one...

00:17:25.879 --> 00:17:29.632 position:50% align:center
They were both carefully made
with the wearer in mind.

00:17:29.716 --> 00:17:31.426 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU]
"Ikuto Tsumura."

00:17:31.509 --> 00:17:36.639 position:50% align:center
Igarashi, didn't you have some
problem with this designer, too?

00:17:36.723 --> 00:17:41.019 position:50% align:center
What do you think of his
stuff... as an ex-model?

00:17:41.102 --> 00:17:43.146 position:50% align:center
[IGARASHI]
Well, she's into it.

00:17:43.229 --> 00:17:44.689 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU chuckles]

00:17:44.773 --> 00:17:46.191 position:50% align:center
[SARA]
I totally get it!

00:17:46.274 --> 00:17:49.444 position:50% align:center
When the clothes are really
well-made, it fires you up!

00:17:49.527 --> 00:17:51.154 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA]
A model's aura is a lot like

00:17:51.237 --> 00:17:53.907 position:50% align:center
a drop of water
on drawing paper.

00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:56.618 position:50% align:center
The designer's concept
is like color in the drop,

00:17:56.701 --> 00:17:58.703 position:50% align:center
which permeates everything.

00:17:58.787 --> 00:18:00.080 position:50% align:center
When the model is talented,

00:18:00.163 --> 00:18:02.749 position:50% align:center
the drawing paper is
completely saturated.

00:18:02.832 --> 00:18:04.042 position:50% align:center
When that happens,

00:18:04.125 --> 00:18:06.586 position:50% align:center
the outfit's concept
comes through powerfully.

00:18:06.670 --> 00:18:08.672 position:50% align:center
Well, I'll say this.
The collection's concept

00:18:08.755 --> 00:18:10.840 position:50% align:center
was apparent from
the very first outfit.

00:18:10.924 --> 00:18:13.093 position:50% align:center
I wonder what's coming next.

00:18:15.512 --> 00:18:18.390 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA]
Aha, a change of direction!

00:18:20.141 --> 00:18:22.018 position:50% align:center
[SARA]
An American look?

00:18:22.102 --> 00:18:26.773 position:50% align:center
[KAZUYA] It's flashy and bold
with a distinct retro feel.

00:18:26.856 --> 00:18:28.733 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
Hmm...

00:18:28.817 --> 00:18:31.111 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA] So if this
is the seventh outfit,

00:18:31.194 --> 00:18:35.281 position:50% align:center
and it looks like Ikuto's
presenting a total of ten looks,

00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:39.786 position:50% align:center
I wonder if he's amping
things up for the finale now.

00:18:39.869 --> 00:18:41.871 position:50% align:center
Usually, you can
bet on the key outfit

00:18:41.955 --> 00:18:45.625 position:50% align:center
being presented either at the
very beginning or at the end.

00:18:45.709 --> 00:18:48.628 position:50% align:center
My bet's on America again
for the eighth outfit.

00:18:48.712 --> 00:18:50.672 position:50% align:center
The ninth look might
be something German,

00:18:50.755 --> 00:18:52.632 position:50% align:center
military style.

00:18:52.716 --> 00:18:55.885 position:50% align:center
And for the finale,
the tenth outfit...

00:18:57.762 --> 00:19:00.682 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA] Well, look at that!
The eighth is Germany?

00:19:00.765 --> 00:19:02.976 position:50% align:center
[KAZUYA]
Throwing some curve balls now.

00:19:03.059 --> 00:19:04.644 position:50% align:center
[SARA]
What's next?

00:19:06.563 --> 00:19:08.773 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA] What? France
for the ninth outfit?

00:19:08.857 --> 00:19:11.651 position:50% align:center
A brilliant aristocratic style.

00:19:11.735 --> 00:19:15.947 position:50% align:center
[KAZUYA] The next one is last.
Will it be France again?

00:19:16.031 --> 00:19:18.700 position:50% align:center
[MAI] Everyone expects
France for the finale--

00:19:18.783 --> 00:19:20.535 position:50% align:center
no doubt about that.

00:19:20.618 --> 00:19:22.579 position:50% align:center
So it's a concept
that deliberately

00:19:22.662 --> 00:19:26.708 position:50% align:center
defies expectations. Bold.

00:19:26.791 --> 00:19:29.586 position:50% align:center
Makes me wonder who
he learned it from.

00:19:29.669 --> 00:19:32.047 position:50% align:center
This designer's
focused on being unisex.

00:19:32.130 --> 00:19:34.007 position:50% align:center
Harmony of the genders.

00:19:34.090 --> 00:19:37.052 position:50% align:center
So the tenth must be...

00:19:40.555 --> 00:19:42.515 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
The final outfit.

00:19:42.599 --> 00:19:44.267 position:50% align:center
This is it!

00:19:48.355 --> 00:19:50.106 position:50% align:center
Take it away!

00:19:51.358 --> 00:19:53.902 position:50% align:center
[CROWD chattering]

00:19:53.985 --> 00:19:57.572 position:50% align:center
[JUDGES gasping]

00:19:57.655 --> 00:19:59.449 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:19:59.532 --> 00:20:01.576 position:50% align:center
[MAI] Stripped of any
trace of pretension,

00:20:01.659 --> 00:20:06.581 position:50% align:center
a universal style that belongs
to all and defies any concept.

00:20:06.664 --> 00:20:09.668 position:50% align:center
Clothing for anyone.

00:20:09.751 --> 00:20:11.503 position:50% align:center
Good work.

00:20:11.586 --> 00:20:14.214 position:50% align:center
I think I would've
done the same.

00:20:14.297 --> 00:20:17.175 position:50% align:center
[CROWD whispers]

00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:20.512 position:50% align:center
[KINU] Nothing unnecessary,
the ultimate minimalism.

00:20:20.595 --> 00:20:22.013 position:50% align:center
[TAKAOKA]
Making minimalist clothing

00:20:22.097 --> 00:20:24.849 position:50% align:center
is actually a
tremendous challenge.

00:20:24.933 --> 00:20:27.143 position:50% align:center
You could compare
it to cooking meat.

00:20:27.227 --> 00:20:30.438 position:50% align:center
You don't necessarily need other
ingredients to go with it

00:20:30.522 --> 00:20:33.191 position:50% align:center
or a strong sauce to obscure it.

00:20:33.274 --> 00:20:36.277 position:50% align:center
You simply sew the
material as it is.

00:20:36.361 --> 00:20:40.865 position:50% align:center
[MAI] A reminder that everything
depends on the creator's talent.

00:20:40.949 --> 00:20:42.701 position:50% align:center
He got us, didn't he?

00:20:42.784 --> 00:20:44.035 position:50% align:center
He sure did!

00:20:44.119 --> 00:20:46.287 position:50% align:center
I never would've
expected that finale!

00:20:46.371 --> 00:20:48.707 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I didn't see
it coming, either.

00:20:48.790 --> 00:20:51.292 position:50% align:center
He surprised everyone
with that last look.

00:20:51.376 --> 00:20:53.253 position:50% align:center
Ikuto Tsumura.

00:20:53.336 --> 00:20:55.880 position:50% align:center
It says he's a
non-student participant.

00:20:55.964 --> 00:20:57.507 position:50% align:center
He doesn't go here?

00:20:57.590 --> 00:21:00.176 position:50% align:center
It says he's still
in high school.

00:21:00.260 --> 00:21:02.053 position:50% align:center
The slightest wrinkle
tends to stick out

00:21:02.137 --> 00:21:04.472 position:50% align:center
like a sore thumb in
this type of clothing.

00:21:04.556 --> 00:21:06.266 position:50% align:center
So if the pattern
was a millimeter off,

00:21:06.349 --> 00:21:08.018 position:50% align:center
it would ruin the whole outfit.

00:21:08.101 --> 00:21:10.395 position:50% align:center
But look at that
beautiful silhouette.

00:21:10.478 --> 00:21:13.148 position:50% align:center
It's very well-made.

00:21:13.231 --> 00:21:14.607 position:50% align:center
Here ya go!

00:21:14.691 --> 00:21:17.694 position:50% align:center
My, what's this? Are you saying
you made this for Mommy?

00:21:17.777 --> 00:21:19.446 position:50% align:center
Honey, this is amazing!

00:21:19.529 --> 00:21:21.948 position:50% align:center
Hard to believe this
is your first garment!

00:21:22.032 --> 00:21:23.658 position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:21:23.742 --> 00:21:26.202 position:50% align:center
I should maybe iron it though.

00:21:28.038 --> 00:21:30.623 position:50% align:center
[ICHIKA gasps]

00:21:30.707 --> 00:21:35.712 position:50% align:center
[CROWD clapping]

00:21:38.673 --> 00:21:39.466 position:50% align:center
Aoi?

00:21:39.549 --> 00:21:40.508 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:21:40.592 --> 00:21:43.219 position:50% align:center
Hold Ichika for a second.

00:21:43.303 --> 00:21:44.721 position:50% align:center
You okay?

00:21:52.437 --> 00:21:56.316 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO]
Ikuto! That was amazing!

00:21:56.399 --> 00:21:59.069 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:59.152 --> 00:22:00.403 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO cries]

00:22:00.487 --> 00:22:03.490 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO] You've come
such a long way, kiddo.

00:22:05.033 --> 00:22:07.285 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO]
And mostly on your own,

00:22:07.369 --> 00:22:11.164 position:50% align:center
since I couldn't be there for
you the way I wanted to be.

00:22:12.916 --> 00:22:15.543 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO] That's why
I promised myself to smile

00:22:15.627 --> 00:22:18.171 position:50% align:center
and never shed a tear
in front of you kids,

00:22:18.254 --> 00:22:20.382 position:50% align:center
so you wouldn't
let it get you down.

00:22:20.465 --> 00:22:22.258 position:50% align:center
Wait. You're crying?

00:22:22.342 --> 00:22:24.636 position:50% align:center
What is happening?

00:22:24.719 --> 00:22:26.262 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO]
But...

00:22:26.346 --> 00:22:29.474 position:50% align:center
...today's an exception, okay?

00:22:29.557 --> 00:22:30.975 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO gasps]

00:22:34.646 --> 00:22:37.816 position:50% align:center
[CROWD clapping]

00:22:37.899 --> 00:22:39.734 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Thank you.

00:24:16.039 --> 00:24:18.291 position:50% align:center
[CROWD clapping]

00:24:18.375 --> 00:24:20.418 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Listen to that applause.

00:24:20.502 --> 00:24:21.503 position:50% align:center
Ikuto...

00:24:21.586 --> 00:24:23.922 position:50% align:center
I guess he must've
had a good show.

00:24:24.005 --> 00:24:25.465 position:50% align:center
I think you're right.

00:24:25.548 --> 00:24:27.509 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Dude, talking to myself.

00:24:27.592 --> 00:24:30.637 position:50% align:center
Oh, shoot, I'm sorry.
Should I not respond, then?

00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:32.514 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Well, duh.

00:24:32.597 --> 00:24:35.183 position:50% align:center
Right, 'cause, I mean, it's
not like we're collaborating

00:24:35.266 --> 00:24:38.103 position:50% align:center
as friends or anything,
I guess...

00:24:38.186 --> 00:24:40.605 position:50% align:center
Exactly.

00:24:40.689 --> 00:24:42.774 position:50% align:center
You better fulfill my promise.

00:24:42.857 --> 00:24:44.484 position:50% align:center
[KOKORO]
Mm.

00:24:44.567 --> 00:24:48.196 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER A]
Next up, Kokoro Hasegawa.

00:24:48.279 --> 00:24:49.823 position:50% align:center
Let's go.

00:24:51.533 --> 00:24:53.576 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
We're aren't friends, Kokoro.

00:24:53.660 --> 00:24:58.164 position:50% align:center
We may be on the same team,
but you're still my rival.

00:24:58.248 --> 00:24:59.916 position:50% align:center
Next time, "The Promise."